code_changes.content:
{
  "buggy_files": [
    "drivers/ata/libata-core.c"
  ],
  "buggy_functions": [
    "ata_device_blacklist",
    "ata_dev_config_ncq_send_recv"
  ],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The Samsung SSD 860 EVO causes queued TRIM (FPDMA SEND) command timeouts. The root cause is that the device is missing from the ata_device_blacklist[] array with the ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag. Similar Samsung models (840, 850) are already in the blacklist (libata-core.c lines 4562-4565) with this flag to disable queued TRIM. Without this flag, the device's FPDMA DSM TRIM capability is not disabled. In ata_dev_config_ncq_send_recv() (line 2197), the code checks 'dev->horkage & ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM' (line 2218) to decide whether to clear the TRIM support bit. Since Samsung 860 EVO doesn't have this horkage flag set, queued TRIM is attempted, leading to timeouts on ASMedia ASM1062 SATA controllers. The fix requires adding Samsung SSD 860 to ata_device_blacklist[] with ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM | ATA_HORKAGE_ZERO_AFTER_TRIM flags, similar to the 840 and 850 entries."
}

